1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,320
I figured it out!

2
00:00:01,320 --> 00:00:04,280
You switch between being yourself and Sun
every time you wake up!

3
00:00:05,210 --> 00:00:06,010
Teacher Solar!

4
00:00:06,010 --> 00:00:09,520
I've said it hundreds of times.
My name is Sun!

5
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:11,150
- Sponge bath.
- Huh?

6
00:00:11,150 --> 00:00:12,850
My magic word.

7
00:00:12,850 --> 00:00:15,220
I mean... can you help me?

8
00:00:15,220 --> 00:00:17,770
You're the best!
You let others help you now, right?

9
00:00:17,770 --> 00:00:21,370
Our teacher Solar has to take on
the character of Little Sun on some days.

10
00:00:21,370 --> 00:00:23,540
Okay!

11
00:00:25,550 --> 00:00:27,030
But don't worry.

12
00:00:27,030 --> 00:00:29,283
I'm going to help you get better
no matter what.

13
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,680
[Today Is A Good Day]

14
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:41,690
Uncle!

15
00:00:41,690 --> 00:00:42,880
Wake up!

16
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:45,440
It's 7 AM. Don't you have to go to work?

17
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,110
Wake up. Come on!

18
00:00:48,110 --> 00:00:50,760
Come on! Come on! Come on!

19
00:01:06,910 --> 00:01:08,210
Hey.

20
00:01:08,210 --> 00:01:09,340
It's only 6 AM.

21
00:01:09,340 --> 00:01:10,670
Why wake me up so early?

22
00:01:10,670 --> 00:01:13,980
If I hadn't, you'd be late for work again.

23
00:01:14,930 --> 00:01:17,510
And this is the little troublemaker

24
00:01:17,510 --> 00:01:20,280
I have to deal with every other day.

25
00:01:21,050 --> 00:01:25,230
I'm trying to figure out
how to adjust and live with Sun,

26
00:01:25,230 --> 00:01:30,140
even though I don't understand
what being a kid is like at all.

27
00:01:31,990 --> 00:01:37,420
Luckily, Solar came up with a brilliant way
for me to handle it.

28
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:41,390
Have you ever wondered

29
00:01:41,390 --> 00:01:45,740
why sometimes you sleep for days,
not knowing what day or time it is?

30
00:01:45,740 --> 00:01:49,320
And have you ever wondered
why people keep calling you...

31
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:51,740
Solar?

32
00:01:51,740 --> 00:01:53,930
Solar!

33
00:01:53,930 --> 00:01:56,920
The truth is I'm...

34
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,240
a cop from the future!
[Future Police Department]

35
00:02:03,420 --> 00:02:08,500
My job is to take down
the devils attacking our world.

36
00:02:11,420 --> 00:02:15,400
Unfortunately, I got hit by a curse...

37
00:02:18,450 --> 00:02:20,257
that makes me from the future,

38
00:02:20,257 --> 00:02:23,440
and you from the past,
switch every other day.

39
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:24,940
But don't worry.

40
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:27,790
I'm trying to find a way to break the curse.

41
00:02:27,790 --> 00:02:34,000
I've gotten help from
these kind adults from the future!

42
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,500
You have an important mission too.

43
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:40,270
That is, blend in at school
as smoothly as possible,

44
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:42,450
and learn to live with others.

45
00:02:42,450 --> 00:02:43,627
Most importantly,

46
00:02:43,627 --> 00:02:48,550
you have to listen to
these three kind adults from the future.

47
00:02:51,660 --> 00:02:53,800
This is a top secret mission.

48
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,900
Do not tell anyone.

49
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:59,460
Sun, you think you've got this?

50
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:05,390
If you do, let's fist bump!

51
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,560
[Sukhum Udom Rak School]

52
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,140
Alright.

53
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:24,480
First word.

54
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:27,120
H is for Happy.

55
00:04:45,130 --> 00:04:47,040
Clap your hands.

56
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,730
Good job.

57
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:55,140
- Looks like the kids have now opened up,
- Next one.

58
00:04:55,140 --> 00:04:57,320
And really believe that Solar is Sun.

59
00:04:57,320 --> 00:05:00,205
Just like Solar predicted,

60
00:05:00,205 --> 00:05:04,890
everything is going well,
and we're ready for the next step.

61
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:12,350
Uncle.

62
00:05:12,350 --> 00:05:13,700
Yes?

63
00:05:15,860 --> 00:05:18,180
What are we doing here?

64
00:05:19,460 --> 00:05:21,480
We're here to see a doctor.

65
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:28,560
She's a kind adult from the future,

66
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:31,900
and she knows how to break the devil's curse.

67
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,140
No! No!

68
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:36,740
I don't want to see the doctor! Let me go!

69
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,210
Sun! We have an important mission to do.

70
00:05:44,210 --> 00:05:45,860
No! I don't want to do the mission anymore!

71
00:05:45,860 --> 00:05:48,400
I don't want to see the doctor!
I don't want to get a shot. No!

72
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,580
I don't want this anymore!

73
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:53,950
- Sun, we have a mission...
- There'll be no shots.

74
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,690
Little Sun, right?

75
00:05:59,690 --> 00:06:01,030
Don't worry.

76
00:06:01,030 --> 00:06:04,860
We're just going to have
a fun little chat today, okay?

77
00:06:04,860 --> 00:06:07,180
How old are you?

78
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:11,690
S... S... Seven.

79
00:06:11,690 --> 00:06:14,610
Oh, your voice is shaking.

80
00:06:14,610 --> 00:06:16,690
Are you scared?

81
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:18,850
No.

82
00:06:18,850 --> 00:06:21,410
I just want to pee.

83
00:06:21,410 --> 00:06:22,940
Oh, why didn't you tell me?

84
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:26,380
I'll have the nurse
take you to the bathroom now.

85
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,760
[Toilet]

86
00:07:01,476 --> 00:07:03,940
Is Sun in here?
He's been gone for a while.

87
00:07:03,940 --> 00:07:06,530
- Yes, well...
- Ouch!

88
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:16,800
Sun! What are you doing?

89
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,620
I don't want to see the doctor, Uncle!

90
00:07:18,620 --> 00:07:22,620
Help pull me down!

91
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:24,370
Help pull me down, Uncle!

92
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:55,300
How much longer are you going to sulk?

93
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:58,270
I told you we need to see the doctor.

94
00:08:03,290 --> 00:08:04,671
Uncle.

95
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:08,000
Am I sick?

96
00:08:11,590 --> 00:08:13,590
You're not sick.

97
00:08:13,590 --> 00:08:16,880
You're just cursed,

98
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:19,500
and the doctor knows how to break it.

99
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:22,950
So you won't have to keep switching
with Solar all the time.

100
00:08:24,180 --> 00:08:25,803
So...

101
00:08:26,620 --> 00:08:29,080
if the curse is lifted,

102
00:08:29,940 --> 00:08:33,100
does that mean I can come out
and play like this all the time?

103
00:08:38,260 --> 00:08:39,780
Yeah.

104
00:08:42,110 --> 00:08:43,640
Really?

105
00:08:46,470 --> 00:08:48,140
Fine, I'll believe you.

106
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:53,200
Good job.

107
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,660
Uncle has something for you.

108
00:09:06,685 --> 00:09:08,115
Here.

109
00:09:09,330 --> 00:09:13,060
- Wow!
- All these toys are just for you, Sun.

110
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:14,950
- Really?
- Yeah.

111
00:09:14,950 --> 00:09:16,250
I can play with any of these?

112
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,100
Any of them.

113
00:09:19,340 --> 00:09:20,930
Yay!

114
00:09:23,620 --> 00:09:26,720
Wow! Yay!

115
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:56,710
- Hi, Aunt.
- Pobmek, how are you?

116
00:09:56,710 --> 00:09:59,650
You've taken Solar
to see a psychotherapist, right?

117
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:01,060
Yes.

118
00:10:02,460 --> 00:10:05,890
Well, Solar...

119
00:10:05,890 --> 00:10:10,660
It sounds very fantasy-like,

120
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:14,070
but it could be a case of age regression.

121
00:10:14,070 --> 00:10:18,770
As children,
if we experience something deeply traumatic,

122
00:10:18,770 --> 00:10:21,306
our bodies create defense mechanisms

123
00:10:21,306 --> 00:10:23,794
to protect our minds from breaking down.

124
00:10:24,580 --> 00:10:25,820
Do you have any idea

125
00:10:25,820 --> 00:10:31,230
if he experienced something like that
as a child?

126
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:36,220
I've talked to Solar
about his childhood before,

127
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:39,700
but he said he doesn't remember anything
from when he was a child.

128
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:41,760
The car accident

129
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:44,310
is probably the most traumatic for him.

130
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:51,610
So, I want to know what Solar went through
when he was a kid, Aunt.

131
00:10:55,770 --> 00:10:59,400
I have to go. I'll call you back.

132
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:07,880
Sun! What are you doing?

133
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,800
Uncle! Look!

134
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,700
I made a flying robot!

135
00:11:19,130 --> 00:11:21,870
You can play with any toy, but not that one!

136
00:11:26,170 --> 00:11:27,800
Ouch!

137
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:30,470
Damn...

138
00:11:30,470 --> 00:11:31,580
Ouch!

139
00:11:31,580 --> 00:11:32,860
Ow!

140
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:34,770
Ouch!

141
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:39,720
[To Do List]
[Sun - Solar]

142
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:50,000
Did you just wake up,
or have you not slept at all?

143
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:53,510
I haven't slept. Look!

144
00:11:57,620 --> 00:11:59,552
Jeez!

145
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,600
I can't take this anymore.

146
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:06,360
If you don't get back to your old self soon,

147
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:10,350
our room's going to turn
into a toy graveyard.

148
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:22,740
What did the psychotherapist say?

149
00:12:23,540 --> 00:12:26,340
There might be a way to help you...

150
00:12:27,950 --> 00:12:31,780
if we know what you went through
in your childhood.

151
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:34,150
Really?

152
00:12:38,220 --> 00:12:40,279
As I said,

153
00:12:41,916 --> 00:12:44,180
I really don't remember anything.

154
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:48,050
Yeah, I already told her that.

155
00:12:48,050 --> 00:12:50,430
Then I called your mom last night.

156
00:12:50,430 --> 00:12:51,980
What did my mom say?

157
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:53,540
I didn't get to hear anything.

158
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:56,372
Sun wrecked the room first.

159
00:12:57,170 --> 00:12:59,470
And my phone's broken.

160
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:04,420
If you talk to your mom,

161
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:08,700
can you ask if she knows anything?

162
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:15,680
Please!

163
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:20,690
Please make Solar
go back to normal next month,

164
00:13:20,690 --> 00:13:22,500
and never let Sun come back again!

165
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:23,930
Amen!

166
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:38,660
Maybe having Sun around...

167
00:13:39,868 --> 00:13:42,490
is a good thing.

168
00:13:48,980 --> 00:13:54,120
At least you found something
you thought you lost a long time ago.

169
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,700
Yeah.

170
00:13:57,700 --> 00:13:59,190
It's good.

171
00:13:59,190 --> 00:14:01,500
Not!

172
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:05,580
Look! Sun glued the robot.

173
00:14:05,580 --> 00:14:08,650
And I don't even know if the umbrella
is breaking or not.

174
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:23,560
I'm tired of Sun!

175
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:25,180
[Sukhum Udom Rak School]

176
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:26,240
Alright, everyone.

177
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,590
[Rainy]
Read this together.

178
00:14:27,590 --> 00:14:30,320
Rainy!

179
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,320
Let's spell it together.

180
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:36,040
R... A... I... N...

181
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,870
Wow, man.

182
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:42,070
I know teaching doesn't pay that well,

183
00:14:42,070 --> 00:14:44,870
but you don't have to be this frugal.

184
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:48,130
Sun did that, didn't he?

185
00:14:48,130 --> 00:14:50,000
Come on. Don't be upset.

186
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,470
The kid needed to use his imagination.

187
00:14:52,470 --> 00:14:55,640
You can just get a new umbrella
like this one, right?

188
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:58,440
It's not hard to get a new one,

189
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:03,680
but there is no other umbrella like it
in the world.

190
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,780
Hello, Mom.

191
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:18,060
It's not this box.

192
00:15:18,770 --> 00:15:21,020
My book box has a sticker on it.

193
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:23,660
This is the box of old stuff
I'm throwing away.

194
00:15:23,660 --> 00:15:26,660
Really? They all look the same.
[Sung by me!]

195
00:15:26,660 --> 00:15:29,320
Let me bring it to your dorm tonight.

196
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,490
It's okay, Mom.

197
00:15:30,490 --> 00:15:32,140
I don't need it now.

198
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:34,710
Alright then. Have you eaten...

199
00:15:34,710 --> 00:15:38,310
I need to study. I have to go.

200
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:45,340
Why is it raining so hard?

201
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:49,770
What's going on? It's raining every day!

202
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,160
Here.

203
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:55,750
It's the rainy season in Thailand.

204
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:57,420
Why didn't you carry an umbrella?

205
00:15:57,420 --> 00:15:59,080
I forgot.

206
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:02,720
I was going to cut through the building,
but that didn't work.

207
00:16:08,860 --> 00:16:10,450
Is that your umbrella?

208
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:12,780
Yeah.

209
00:16:12,780 --> 00:16:14,460
It's my old one.

210
00:16:15,450 --> 00:16:16,800
Let me see.

211
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,160
Hey!

212
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:22,764
Hey.

213
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:25,300
I'm on this too.

214
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:26,740
What do you mean?

215
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:29,310
Here, this is the sun.

216
00:16:29,310 --> 00:16:31,350
It gives solar energy.

217
00:16:33,490 --> 00:16:35,730
Unbelievable.

218
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,439
Hey!

219
00:16:46,190 --> 00:16:48,150
There's another one.

220
00:17:21,470 --> 00:17:24,270
You can take it.

221
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:34,730
No, I'll pass.

222
00:17:39,070 --> 00:17:41,039
You should keep it for yourself.

223
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:52,052
Since that day,

224
00:17:52,052 --> 00:17:57,460
I'd been using this umbrella
as an excuse to get close to Solar.

225
00:18:46,570 --> 00:18:48,140
Wow.

226
00:18:48,810 --> 00:18:52,100
What a romantic prop, man.

227
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:57,560
Oh, now I get why you're so mad at Sun.

228
00:18:57,560 --> 00:19:01,550
I get that Sun didn't mean it,

229
00:19:01,550 --> 00:19:05,030
but I can't just not feel anything.

230
00:19:05,030 --> 00:19:09,500
So, I want to help Solar recover
as soon as possible.

231
00:19:11,060 --> 00:19:13,378
That's so fetch!

232
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:21,080
Elsa, what are you writing down, sweetie?

233
00:19:25,590 --> 00:19:27,220
Burn book?

234
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:30,650
Is that for writing down
your friends' secrets?

235
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:33,160
That's evil.

236
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:38,410
To be the queen bee,
you obviously need a weapon.

237
00:19:38,410 --> 00:19:41,290
We don't go around using force anymore.

238
00:19:41,290 --> 00:19:43,737
We use psychology.

239
00:19:45,340 --> 00:19:47,850
Is this really a student in my school?

240
00:19:47,850 --> 00:19:51,360
Sun is new,
so I have to take some notes on him.

241
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:53,660
If I know what issues my friend has,

242
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:56,210
I can handle them better.

243
00:19:57,950 --> 00:19:59,780
Elsa.

244
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:02,280
We're going pee-pee. Wanna come with us?

245
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:03,860
Of course.

246
00:20:03,860 --> 00:20:06,840
Please excuse me, teachers.

247
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:09,180
Let's go, girls.

248
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:26,990
[Sun: Naughty but handsome.
But cuter than handsome. Wanna adopt him]

249
00:20:26,990 --> 00:20:28,180
Elsa,

250
00:20:28,180 --> 00:20:29,930
I thought you were taking notes
on your friends' issues,

251
00:20:29,930 --> 00:20:31,700
but there's nothing here.

252
00:20:33,990 --> 00:20:37,610
If you want there to be something,
there can be.

253
00:20:37,610 --> 00:20:40,540
When you spend a long time with something,

254
00:20:40,540 --> 00:20:44,030
you tend to change along with it.

255
00:20:44,030 --> 00:20:46,310
That's all I'll say.

256
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:50,760
Wait, what?

257
00:20:57,050 --> 00:21:00,590
I think I've found a solution.

258
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:06,140
That solution is...

259
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:07,906
[Plan To Get Solar Back]

260
00:21:12,060 --> 00:21:15,670
We need to keep him as Solar
as long as possible.

261
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:19,000
And get Sun to bed as early as possible.

262
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,480
If we keep doing that,
[Sun: 50%, Solar: 50%]

263
00:21:20,770 --> 00:21:22,820
Solar will be with us longer.

264
00:21:22,820 --> 00:21:26,800
And Sun might just disappear for good.
[Solar: 100%]

265
00:21:31,940 --> 00:21:33,500
Genius!

266
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:36,810
You were a first-class honors student
with a gold medal, after all!

267
00:21:36,810 --> 00:21:40,340
But will it really work?

268
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:44,040
If we don't try, we'll never know.

269
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:46,620
We don't know Solar's past trauma anyway,

270
00:21:46,620 --> 00:21:49,490
so I think it's worth a try.

271
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:55,870
Solar.

272
00:21:57,740 --> 00:21:58,970
Solar!

273
00:21:58,970 --> 00:22:00,300
Huh?

274
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,550
Are you okay?

275
00:22:13,950 --> 00:22:15,390
Yeah.

276
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:18,650
Let's do it.

277
00:22:18,650 --> 00:22:20,210
Deal!

278
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:52,160
[Sun's Day]

279
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:03,100
Uncle, what are you doing?

280
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:05,900
Getting ready to do something fun, of course.

281
00:23:07,390 --> 00:23:11,030
Here are your new shoes. You like them?

282
00:23:11,030 --> 00:23:13,740
These are so cool, Uncle.

283
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:15,950
They're mine?

284
00:23:15,950 --> 00:23:18,750
Let's go release some energy!

285
00:23:22,990 --> 00:23:24,370
- Go!
- Faster! Faster!

286
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:25,820
Go!

287
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,200
[Day 1 Without Sleep]

288
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:40,120
[Solar's Day]

289
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:42,840
[6 Hours Without Sleep]

290
00:23:43,140 --> 00:23:45,280
Since you're not going to sleep,

291
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:47,310
can you help me summarize the curriculum?

292
00:23:47,310 --> 00:23:48,700
Sure.

293
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:50,720
Just for Grade 2, right?

294
00:23:51,780 --> 00:23:54,440
Grade 1 all the way to Grade 6.

295
00:23:58,990 --> 00:24:00,740
I'll leave it to you.

296
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:12,080
[12 Hours Without Sleep]

297
00:24:14,750 --> 00:24:16,010
Here.

298
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:27,840
[Sun's Day]

299
00:24:28,070 --> 00:24:29,450
Move!

300
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:18,240
[Solar's Day Again!]

301
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:20,590
We broke the record.
[Sun: 30%, Solar: 70%]

302
00:25:20,590 --> 00:25:23,040
Solar hasn't slept for 48 hours.

303
00:25:23,040 --> 00:25:24,880
[38, 40, 42, 44 Hours]

304
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:30,240
Soon, Solar will get his body back.
[45, 46, 47, 48 Hours]

305
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,120
Oh!

306
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:38,440
But until then,
won't he have to stay awake all week?

307
00:25:40,450 --> 00:25:42,438
Pobmek.

308
00:25:46,540 --> 00:25:49,810
We're leaving.

309
00:25:49,810 --> 00:25:51,620
Let me walk you out.

310
00:25:57,060 --> 00:25:58,740
If it's too much,
don't force yourself, Solar.

311
00:25:58,740 --> 00:26:00,550
You don't want to collapse.

312
00:26:00,550 --> 00:26:02,220
Okay.

313
00:26:02,220 --> 00:26:04,120
Thanks a lot, guys.

314
00:26:04,120 --> 00:26:06,740
Bye. I'm exhausted.

315
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:30,080
[Solar]
[Mom, are you free this Sunday?]

316
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:34,760
[Mom]
[For my son, I'm always free]

317
00:26:44,730 --> 00:26:46,380
Come on.

318
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:49,060
Just push through for another 12 hours,

319
00:26:49,060 --> 00:26:51,300
then nap tomorrow afternoon.

320
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:57,700
So that means on Sunday,
I'll probably wake up as Little Sun.

321
00:27:00,551 --> 00:27:02,160
Yeah.

322
00:27:06,630 --> 00:27:09,680
Okay. I'm going to wash my face.

323
00:27:10,460 --> 00:27:11,930
I'll be right back.

324
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:26,160
[To Do List]
[Saturday - Sun, Sunday - Sun]

325
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:35,080
[P.S.]

326
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:46,080
[Allergy Medicine]
[May cause drowsiness]

327
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:05,700
What are you doing?

328
00:28:14,780 --> 00:28:19,220
Solar, are you going to take medicine
to sleep?

329
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:27,430
Why are you doing this?

330
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:30,920
You're almost getting your body back.

331
00:28:33,620 --> 00:28:34,770
Don't you want to recover?

332
00:28:34,770 --> 00:28:36,770
Why wouldn't I want to?

333
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:43,807
But am I gonna die
if I have to keep doing this over and over?

334
00:28:49,210 --> 00:28:53,810
I'm glad everyone's trying to help me.

335
00:28:58,890 --> 00:29:00,900
But I feel like this is forcing it.

336
00:29:03,610 --> 00:29:06,410
Everything just feels wrong.

337
00:29:07,950 --> 00:29:09,630
You know what?

338
00:29:10,260 --> 00:29:12,026
Every day I wake up,

339
00:29:15,038 --> 00:29:17,490
I don't feel happy at all.

340
00:29:25,820 --> 00:29:28,740
Are we being too harsh on Little Sun?

341
00:29:30,780 --> 00:29:32,700
Clap your hands!

342
00:29:34,530 --> 00:29:37,250
- Really?
- Yeah.

343
00:29:37,250 --> 00:29:39,360
I can play with any of these?

344
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:45,360
I might not be able to communicate with him,

345
00:29:47,550 --> 00:29:52,370
but I can feel that
he's not okay with this at all.

346
00:29:58,290 --> 00:30:02,200
Do we really need to rush
and push him out of our lives like this?

347
00:30:14,770 --> 00:30:16,300
Pobmek.

348
00:30:20,790 --> 00:30:24,860
Do you know why I love you?

349
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:40,500
Solar!

350
00:30:46,430 --> 00:30:48,740
I knew you'd be here.

351
00:30:51,130 --> 00:30:53,609
Come on. Let's go back to our room.

352
00:30:53,609 --> 00:30:54,990
Let's go.

353
00:31:32,890 --> 00:31:37,410
Oh, when's that going to dry?

354
00:32:03,140 --> 00:32:04,620
Turn around.

355
00:32:06,995 --> 00:32:08,490
I'll dry your hair.

356
00:32:19,020 --> 00:32:20,508
So...

357
00:32:21,728 --> 00:32:23,820
you already got a new umbrella?

358
00:32:28,670 --> 00:32:32,860
Yeah... for a while now.

359
00:32:41,460 --> 00:32:44,620
So that means...

360
00:32:45,740 --> 00:32:47,210
Yeah.

361
00:32:48,387 --> 00:32:50,360
I just wanted to know...

362
00:32:51,730 --> 00:32:53,875
how long you'll keep picking me up.

363
00:32:59,780 --> 00:33:01,375
Well, do you know now?

364
00:33:11,170 --> 00:33:12,720
Yeah.

365
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:17,670
Thank you for being consistent.

366
00:33:22,260 --> 00:33:23,560
Why are you laughing?

367
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:25,970
Turn your face the other way.
I'm going to dry your hair.

368
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:34,010
Turn around!

369
00:33:34,810 --> 00:33:39,460
I love you because you're consistent.

370
00:33:40,690 --> 00:33:42,990
You never rush.

371
00:33:43,700 --> 00:33:46,907
But if we keep rushing
to speed up my recovery,

372
00:33:46,907 --> 00:33:49,230
and all end up exhausted like this,

373
00:33:52,140 --> 00:33:54,410
I don't think that's the right way.

374
00:33:58,460 --> 00:34:00,230
Besides,

375
00:34:01,870 --> 00:34:05,190
we might forget
what's important along the way.

376
00:34:17,980 --> 00:34:19,451
Sunday...

377
00:34:22,308 --> 00:34:24,290
is our anniversary.

378
00:34:26,110 --> 00:34:27,780
Exactly.

379
00:34:28,700 --> 00:34:31,830
That's why I want to sleep now,

380
00:34:31,830 --> 00:34:35,750
so I can wake up as myself on Sunday.

381
00:34:37,730 --> 00:34:39,720
So I can be with you.

382
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:16,180
I hope we get to be together this Sunday.

383
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:22,640
[Sun]

384
00:35:28,240 --> 00:35:31,000
Oh, Uncle.

385
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:32,710
Aren't you going to work?

386
00:35:32,710 --> 00:35:33,830
You're going to be late.

387
00:35:33,830 --> 00:35:34,900
I'm not going to be late.

388
00:35:34,900 --> 00:35:37,460
It's Sunday at noon.

389
00:35:39,740 --> 00:35:42,860
You slept for almost two full days.

390
00:35:42,860 --> 00:35:45,240
Really?

391
00:35:49,940 --> 00:35:51,570
That's good.

392
00:35:51,570 --> 00:35:53,750
I had a good, deep sleep.

393
00:35:53,750 --> 00:35:55,760
What should we do today, Uncle?

394
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:56,980
Do we have to go running again?

395
00:35:56,980 --> 00:36:00,130
No. We'll just stay here.

396
00:36:00,130 --> 00:36:02,380
You can play with the toys.

397
00:36:02,380 --> 00:36:07,690
Consider it a reward
for obeying me the whole week.

398
00:36:09,610 --> 00:36:11,000
Really, Uncle?

399
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:12,580
Do you mean it?

400
00:36:12,580 --> 00:36:14,510
- Yes.
- Oh!

401
00:36:14,510 --> 00:36:16,900
Yay! Yes!

402
00:36:16,900 --> 00:36:18,610
Yay! Yes! Yay!

403
00:36:18,610 --> 00:36:20,440
Here I go!

404
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:22,750
Yay!

405
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:32,680
[Chop it!]
Chop it!

406
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:34,080
Chop it up!

407
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:35,460
Go!

408
00:36:39,260 --> 00:36:41,217
Teacher Jee, Teacher Sodchuen,
I can't hear you!

409
00:36:41,217 --> 00:36:42,250
[Plan To Get Solar Back]
[Delete this file?]

410
00:36:42,250 --> 00:36:44,640
- I'm tired! You go on!
- I can't hear you!

411
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,180
I'm tired!

412
00:37:14,430 --> 00:37:16,730
I'm sorry.

413
00:37:16,730 --> 00:37:19,100
I made you miss celebrating your anniversary
with your boyfriend.

414
00:37:19,100 --> 00:37:21,460
Yeah, I'm sorry.

415
00:37:21,460 --> 00:37:24,260
I think it's all our fault.

416
00:37:27,380 --> 00:37:32,220
Who would've thought Solar would sleep
for two days straight?

417
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:44,400
- Oh, hi, Aunt.
- Surprise!

418
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,900
Let me help you with that.

419
00:37:45,900 --> 00:37:48,670
Thanks. Be careful.

420
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,970
Guys, this is Aunt Pranee.

421
00:37:51,970 --> 00:37:53,260
She's Solar's mom.

422
00:37:53,260 --> 00:37:54,300
Hello.

423
00:37:54,300 --> 00:37:56,999
- Hello, Aunt.
- Hi.

424
00:37:57,795 --> 00:38:00,530
Hey, Aunt. What's this box?

425
00:38:00,530 --> 00:38:06,860
Solar told me that if he didn't call me
before noon on Sunday,

426
00:38:06,860 --> 00:38:10,560
I should come see you here.

427
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:15,720
This box has Solar's childhood toys.

428
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:22,600
He said they might help him recover.

429
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:27,640
Thank you so much.

430
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,110
You're welcome.

431
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:40,950
My son looks so happy.

432
00:38:40,950 --> 00:38:43,540
Do you want me to call him?

433
00:38:43,540 --> 00:38:45,520
No need.

434
00:38:47,500 --> 00:38:49,964
I have something more important.

435
00:38:58,260 --> 00:39:03,340
Solar asked me to make this
for your anniversary.

436
00:39:03,340 --> 00:39:07,560
And... there's this too.

437
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:09,380
Here.

438
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:13,070
Hello!

439
00:39:14,330 --> 00:39:16,930
If you're watching this clip,

440
00:39:16,930 --> 00:39:20,170
that means things didn't go as planned.

441
00:39:20,170 --> 00:39:24,460
I probably didn't wake up on our anniversary.

442
00:39:25,830 --> 00:39:27,290
But it's okay.

443
00:39:27,290 --> 00:39:29,720
I've asked Mom to prepare everything.

444
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:32,110
Get ready.

445
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,710
Pobmek.

446
00:39:38,180 --> 00:39:41,710
Before we know it,
we've already been together for 7 years.

447
00:39:43,210 --> 00:39:48,930
I remember you love
my mom's coconut cake, right?

448
00:39:48,930 --> 00:39:51,660
So I asked her to make a big one for you.

449
00:39:51,660 --> 00:39:54,360
She's going to feed it to you.

450
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:57,080
Open your mouth.

451
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:58,450
Mom!

452
00:39:58,450 --> 00:40:00,810
Are you moving your mouth too?

453
00:40:00,810 --> 00:40:03,290
He knows.

454
00:40:03,290 --> 00:40:09,150
Oh, don't forget to read the notebook
out loud,

455
00:40:09,150 --> 00:40:11,060
so it'll be extra special.

456
00:40:13,740 --> 00:40:15,100
Oh, okay.

457
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:31,760
[Being in the clouds]

458
00:40:38,580 --> 00:40:40,343
"Even though I regret

459
00:40:40,343 --> 00:40:43,620
not being able to
feed you the cake myself this year,

460
00:40:47,700 --> 00:40:57,719
on the bright side,
it makes me realize how much I miss you...

461
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:02,952
when we're not together.

462
00:41:06,540 --> 00:41:09,340
And how much I want to see you.

463
00:41:12,910 --> 00:41:21,740
I don't know if I'll get better next year,

464
00:41:22,660 --> 00:41:30,192
but I promise I'll make it up to you
by making every day I wake up

465
00:41:30,192 --> 00:41:32,860
more special than this anniversary."

466
00:41:38,100 --> 00:41:40,920
Hey, I know you're crying.

467
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:42,990
You're always such a crybaby.

468
00:41:42,990 --> 00:41:45,280
There, there.

469
00:41:45,280 --> 00:41:47,740
Tomorrow, I'll wake up to hug you.

470
00:42:14,660 --> 00:42:17,140
Thank you so much, Aunt,

471
00:42:17,870 --> 00:42:20,670
for coming all the way here.

472
00:42:21,390 --> 00:42:22,990
Are you sure you don't want to stay over?

473
00:42:22,990 --> 00:42:24,390
It's okay.

474
00:42:24,390 --> 00:42:26,810
I'm meeting my SY gang tomorrow.

475
00:42:26,810 --> 00:42:29,170
Huh? Senators of the Year?

476
00:42:29,170 --> 00:42:31,050
You're retired, but still in politics?

477
00:42:31,050 --> 00:42:34,460
SY, as in Senior Years, dear.

478
00:42:35,310 --> 00:42:37,173
If you hadn't clarified,

479
00:42:37,173 --> 00:42:38,870
I would've thought
you meant Sao Y, as in BL girls.

480
00:42:38,870 --> 00:42:40,640
That I already am.

481
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:42,550
He's my bias.

482
00:42:45,130 --> 00:42:52,208
Aunt, I'm sorry for prying.

483
00:42:55,100 --> 00:43:01,192
What did Solar go through as a kid?

484
00:43:02,040 --> 00:43:07,550
As far as I know,
he doesn't have a father, right?

485
00:43:14,340 --> 00:43:16,088
That's right.

486
00:43:20,300 --> 00:43:22,624
Sun's father...

487
00:43:24,824 --> 00:43:27,620
I mean Solar's father...

488
00:43:30,270 --> 00:43:33,928
He left Solar when he was a kid.

489
00:43:35,828 --> 00:43:41,080
Aunt, was his name Sun when he was a kid?

490
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:42,680
Yes.

491
00:43:42,680 --> 00:43:44,490
But why did he have to change it?

492
00:43:44,490 --> 00:43:50,410
He must've heard the name Solar somewhere
and liked it,

493
00:43:50,410 --> 00:43:52,960
so he changed it himself.

494
00:43:54,010 --> 00:43:56,520
That's my ride.

495
00:43:56,520 --> 00:43:59,512
I should go.

496
00:44:01,664 --> 00:44:04,608
- Goodbye.
- Bye, Aunt.

497
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:18,712
Pobmek, I believe that someday,
Solar will recover.

498
00:44:20,300 --> 00:44:22,448
Don't give up.

499
00:44:26,370 --> 00:44:28,056
I won't.

500
00:44:29,180 --> 00:44:31,336
- Bye now.
- Bye.

501
00:44:32,970 --> 00:44:34,512
Safe trip home.

502
00:44:34,512 --> 00:44:36,064
Thanks.

503
00:44:51,470 --> 00:44:53,679
Uncle.

504
00:44:53,679 --> 00:44:55,430
Can I take a look?

505
00:44:55,430 --> 00:44:57,712
I promise I won't break anything this time.

506
00:44:58,910 --> 00:45:01,112
I haven't said anything yet.

507
00:45:03,580 --> 00:45:07,352
Let's see what you loved playing with
when you were a kid.

508
00:45:17,340 --> 00:45:19,568
There are no toys here.

509
00:45:23,304 --> 00:45:24,630
Oh.

510
00:45:24,630 --> 00:45:27,600
What's this, Uncle?
[Sung by me!]

511
00:45:30,080 --> 00:45:32,160
How did it get here?

512
00:45:36,580 --> 00:45:38,070
Is that a music CD?

513
00:45:38,070 --> 00:45:39,660
Play it for me, please.

514
00:45:39,660 --> 00:45:41,360
No.

515
00:45:41,360 --> 00:45:42,592
Play it for me, please.

516
00:45:42,592 --> 00:45:45,464
- No.
- Please!

517
00:45:45,464 --> 00:45:47,656
Let me listen.

518
00:45:47,656 --> 00:45:49,224
- Please!
- Check out something else.

519
00:45:49,224 --> 00:45:50,736
No. I want to listen.

520
00:45:50,736 --> 00:45:52,112
Please!

521
00:45:52,112 --> 00:45:54,620
- Pretty, please!
- Fine.

522
00:45:54,620 --> 00:45:56,528
I'll play it.

523
00:46:15,220 --> 00:46:17,950
"Sung by me!"

524
00:46:17,950 --> 00:46:20,070
Why are you throwing it away?

525
00:46:20,070 --> 00:46:22,830
It's just a normal recording of me singing.

526
00:46:22,830 --> 00:46:24,440
I don't see why I should keep it.

527
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:25,750
Hey.

528
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:28,780
Solar. It's your voice.

529
00:46:28,780 --> 00:46:31,330
It'd be a shame to throw it away.

530
00:46:31,330 --> 00:46:33,070
- Let's listen to it.
- No.

531
00:46:33,070 --> 00:46:34,750
Please.

532
00:46:34,750 --> 00:46:36,380
I promise I won't tease you.

533
00:46:36,380 --> 00:46:37,608
At all.

534
00:46:37,608 --> 00:46:39,656
People who tease always say that.

535
00:46:39,656 --> 00:46:41,730
- No, I'm throwing it away!
- No!

536
00:46:41,730 --> 00:46:44,680
- Solar.
- Come on.

537
00:46:47,690 --> 00:46:50,864
- No teasing.
- Hey, I already promised!

538
00:47:02,928 --> 00:47:05,960
♫ Every second ♫

539
00:47:05,960 --> 00:47:08,848
♫ I will spend on you ♫

540
00:47:08,848 --> 00:47:14,740
♫ However much time passes through ♫

541
00:47:14,740 --> 00:47:20,560
♫ And when the rain falls,
know I'm here next to you ♫

542
00:47:20,560 --> 00:47:22,752
♫ We'll make it together ♫

543
00:47:22,752 --> 00:47:25,496
♫ And that alone will do ♫

544
00:47:25,496 --> 00:47:29,032
Solar.

545
00:47:33,460 --> 00:47:35,104
What's wrong?

546
00:47:37,250 --> 00:47:38,968
I don't know.

547
00:47:40,312 --> 00:47:42,970
My tears just started falling out of nowhere.

548
00:47:45,784 --> 00:47:48,632
♫ Let our story be written in our hearts ♫

549
00:47:48,632 --> 00:47:51,776
♫ 'Cause this love is meant just for us ♫

550
00:47:51,776 --> 00:47:57,016
♫ I will never let your hand go ♫

551
00:47:57,016 --> 00:48:00,560
♫ I will paint and fill the storyline
with you ♫

552
00:48:00,560 --> 00:48:03,968
♫ No matter if the sky turns dark and blue ♫

553
00:48:03,968 --> 00:48:05,736
♫ I will remain right here
beside you, always ♫

554
00:48:05,736 --> 00:48:07,927
What's wrong, Sun?

555
00:48:07,927 --> 00:48:09,336
Sun?

556
00:48:13,620 --> 00:48:15,744
Hey, Sun!

557
00:48:17,110 --> 00:48:19,740
Sun! What's wrong, Sun?

558
00:48:19,740 --> 00:48:22,612
Sun!

559
00:48:23,360 --> 00:48:24,792
Sun!

560
00:48:34,080 --> 00:48:36,728
Sun, what's wrong? You scared me!

561
00:48:44,670 --> 00:48:46,152
Hey.

562
00:48:48,640 --> 00:48:50,440
It's me.

563
00:48:51,302 --> 00:48:52,808
It's Solar.

564
00:48:53,700 --> 00:48:55,091
Huh?

565
00:48:58,060 --> 00:48:59,590
Damn!

566
00:48:59,590 --> 00:49:03,800
This is straight out of a Doraemon episode,
The Snoozy CD!

567
00:49:04,430 --> 00:49:05,848
Who knows?

568
00:49:05,848 --> 00:49:10,620
Your song might just be the thing
that helps Sun turn into Solar faster.

569
00:49:10,620 --> 00:49:12,336
Yay!

570
00:49:12,336 --> 00:49:16,510
Finally, I've found a way to survive!

571
00:49:16,510 --> 00:49:18,928
But what's that song?

572
00:49:18,928 --> 00:49:21,670
Why does it have a sleeping-pill effect?

573
00:49:21,670 --> 00:49:23,768
It's his voice from high school.

574
00:49:23,768 --> 00:49:25,826
He sounded amazing.

575
00:49:26,710 --> 00:49:28,880
Pobmek will play it for you.

576
00:49:39,560 --> 00:49:40,660
Wait.

577
00:49:40,660 --> 00:49:42,920
Are we going to hear it today?

578
00:49:42,920 --> 00:49:44,530
Calm down.

579
00:49:44,530 --> 00:49:47,232
The player is old. It's a bit tricky to open.

580
00:49:56,880 --> 00:49:58,992
Shit!

581
00:50:02,370 --> 00:50:03,688
What have you done?

582
00:50:03,688 --> 00:50:05,180
Pobmek!

583
00:50:05,180 --> 00:50:08,168
I'm going to have to run with Sun again,
aren't I?

584
00:50:15,260 --> 00:50:17,528
Sorry about my boyfriend.

585
00:50:17,528 --> 00:50:18,949
But it's fine.

586
00:50:18,949 --> 00:50:24,624
At least we found out that
the song is our solution, right?

587
00:50:24,624 --> 00:50:26,160
Right.

588
00:50:26,160 --> 00:50:29,220
Let's call it a night. I'm sleepy.

589
00:50:29,220 --> 00:50:30,712
Okay.

590
00:50:33,910 --> 00:50:36,580
Damn!

591
00:50:36,580 --> 00:50:39,640
Comfort me.

592
00:50:39,640 --> 00:50:41,952
You always want me to comfort you.

593
00:50:47,936 --> 00:50:49,416
It's alright.

594
00:50:50,620 --> 00:50:53,149
Let's take it slow, okay?

595
00:50:56,170 --> 00:51:00,340
Since the day isn't over yet,

596
00:51:00,340 --> 00:51:05,352
can we keep celebrating our anniversary
a little longer?

597
00:51:33,790 --> 00:51:36,192
As we promised,

598
00:51:36,980 --> 00:51:41,824
let's not do it until I'm fully recovered.

599
00:51:43,610 --> 00:51:45,460
Alright.

600
00:51:45,460 --> 00:51:49,576
But can I cuddle you all night tonight?

601
00:51:52,460 --> 00:51:53,928
Of course.

602
00:52:11,056 --> 00:52:16,088
Even though we still don't know
when Solar will recover,

603
00:52:16,730 --> 00:52:19,250
if we keep holding hands,

604
00:52:19,250 --> 00:52:25,976
I believe time will heal everything.

605
00:52:35,770 --> 00:52:38,496
It's that time of year again.

606
00:52:38,496 --> 00:52:41,592
The class play day
from the English department.

607
00:52:41,592 --> 00:52:43,952
As long as the kids don't choose Sun
as the director,

608
00:52:43,952 --> 00:52:45,464
it should be easy.

609
00:52:45,464 --> 00:52:48,680
Sun for director!

610
00:52:48,680 --> 00:52:50,240
Squirm harder!

611
00:52:50,240 --> 00:52:51,704
Jeez!

612
00:52:51,704 --> 00:52:53,820
I can't deal with Sun anymore!

613
00:52:53,820 --> 00:52:55,792
Do you remember this?

614
00:52:56,610 --> 00:52:58,088
Am I really going to do okay?

615
00:52:58,088 --> 00:52:59,312
You'll be fine.

616
00:52:59,312 --> 00:53:02,720
As long as you're having fun,
the audience will enjoy it too.

